  "texts": [
    "Ghilardi 1995, Thm.",
    "6.3), KD, T, KD4, and S4 have internal adjointness, whereas K5 and its extensions with the D and/or 4 axioms lack internal adjointness.",
    "It would be interesting to know more about internal adjointness for Kripke-frame incomplete modal logics.So far we have shown that various logics are T -complete by observing that their Lindenbaum algebras are T -BAOs.",
    "In other cases, we may know that a logic is sound and complete with respect to a T -BAO that is not its Lindenbaum algebra.",
    "For example, consider the much-used veiled recession frame [Makinson, 1969, Thomason, 1974a, van Benthem, 1978, Blok, 1979], which is the world frame g = ⟨W, R, A⟩ where W = N, nRm iff n -1 ≤ m, and A is the set of all finite and co-finite subsets of N. It is easy to check that g is a general world frame."
  ],
